**`red-cell-c2-t4ml` (P2 bug — Claude)** — `payload_builder.rs:643`: `add_wstring(out, method)?` writes the user-supplied method string verbatim. The validation at line 634 is case-insensitive, so `method="post"` passes but gets embedded in the Demon binary as `"post"` instead of `"POST"`. HTTP methods are case-sensitive (RFC 7230 §3.1.1); an implant with `method=post` will make non-standard requests that many servers reject — a silently non-functional agent. Fix: `add_wstring(out, &method.to_ascii_uppercase())?`.

No other bugs found.

